"The user browses View 1 at the [Overview] level and learns about the overall distribution of customers grouped by age and satisfaction categories. Next, the user selects an age category and satisfaction group of interest in View 1, affecting View 2. The user observes the churn score distribution in View 2 and explores specific churn score bins, affecting View 3. Then, in View 3 at the [Detail] level, the user identifies clusters of customers or anomalies. Finally, the user gains actionable insights about high-risk age groupings and churn scores in View 4 at the [Insight] level."